/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// Thoughts - 05/04/22 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

With everything that has happened to me in my first 21 years of life, I hated myself a lot. I couldn't find it in me to love myself. I never knew how. 
So when I met Jia Yi, and she seemed to care for and love some part of me, I couldn't believe her. But after a while, after spending so much time with her, 
I started to believe that I deserve to be loved. And then she left. And with that, I feel like my belief that I deserve to be happy, to be loved was fake, and pointless.

I have tried to be a good person my entire life. I may not be the best person on earth, but I did try. I never intentionally hurt anyone, I tried to be kind, generous, 
caring, listening. I like making people I care about happy. That's why I give out so many gifts, because it makes me feel good when I see them happy from my gifts. 
And the person I tried my best to make happy is Jia Yi. The person whose life I tried to improve the most is Jia Yi. I tried my best to make her happy, 
to improve her life, but in the end, she hates me. Doesn't that mean all my effort has gone to waste? That I am not a good person after all? That my best isn't enough, 
and that there isn't a point in me trying to improve the lives of others, and trying to make other people happy?

I hate myself a lot. Then I learnt to love myself. Then I felt as though what I learnt was wrong. And now I hate myself even more. 
If I cannot improve the life of the person I care about the most, if I cannot make the love of my life happy, no matter how much effort I put in, 
how on earth will I ever be able to be a good person by my definition?

I feel like a burden. I feel like I make other people's lives worse. And I feel as though if I stay alive, it will only make things worse. 
So, I really do not see a reason to live anymore. I don't know what is the point in living. I tried and failed to be a good person. I am just a burden

